addr="alex-nelson"
title="Alex Nelson">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link
type="local"
href="ring-0001.xml"
addr="ring-0001"
title="Ring">Ring</fr:link>.</fr:p><fr:ol><fr:li>A <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Maximal Right Ideal</html:dfn> is a proper <fr:link
type="local"
href="ra-0010.xml"
addr="ra-0010"
title="Right ideal of a ring">right ideal</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[I\subset  R]]></fr:tex> such that for any other right ideal <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[J\subseteq  R]]></fr:tex>, if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[I\subseteq  J]]></fr:tex> then either <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[I=J]]></fr:tex> or <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[J=R]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li>
<fr:li>A <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Maximal Left Ideal</html:dfn> is a proper <fr:link
type="local"
href="ra-000Z.xml"
addr="ra-000Z"
title="Left ideal of a ring">left ideal</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[I\subset  R]]></fr:tex> such that for any other left ideal <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[J\subseteq  R]]></fr:tex>, if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[I\subseteq  J]]></fr:tex> then either <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[I=J]]></fr:tex> or <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[J=R]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li>
<fr:li>A <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Maximal (Two-Sided) Ideal</html:dfn> is a proper <fr:link
type="local"
href="ra-0011.xml"
addr="ra-0011"
title="Ideal">ideal</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[I\mathrel {\triangleleft } R]]></fr:tex> such that for any other ideal <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[J\mathrel {\trianglelefteq } R]]></fr:tex>, if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[I\subseteq  J]]></fr:tex> then either <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[I=J]]></fr:tex> or <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[J=R]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li></fr:ol><fr:p>When we drop the condition that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[I]]></fr:tex> is proper, then we have a <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Quasi-Maximal</html:dfn> left/right/two-sided ideal.</fr:p>
 
   
